info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued November 05 at 10:41AM CDT by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...Winds expected to increase across the Fox Valley toward midday and continue this afternoon... A strengthening low pressure system will move rapidly northeast across the forecast area today. South to southwest winds are expected to increase quickly across the southern Fox Valley, including along the I41 and I43 corridors from Green Bay southward. Winds are expected to increase to 20 to 35 mph with localized winds gusts of 55 to 60 mph, especially within bands of organized shower activity racing northeast at 45 to 50 mph. Be prepared for strong winds gusts. High profile vehicles will be especially vulnerable on east-west roadways, such as Highway 29 west of Green Bay. Be alert, slow down and keep firm grip on the steering wheel, especially if driving across bridges and overpasses. Localized strong wind gusts could also knock down large branches and power lines. Stay tuned for later updates.
